			<node ID="ID_600734056" TEXT="HDLC vs PPP . Both HDLC and PPP are data link layer protocols. HDLC (High-Level Data Link Control) is a communication protocol used at the data link layer of computer networks developed by ISO (International Organization for Standardization) and was created out of IBM&#8217;s SDLC (Synchronous Data Link Control)." />
			</node>
