			<node ID="ID_1519914058" TEXT="The major difference between HDLC and PPP is that HDLC is the bit oriented protocol while PPP is the character-oriented protocol. The HDLC and PPP are the crucial data link layer protocols used in WAN (wide area network) where the HDLC can also be implemented with PPP for the efficient results." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1027295859" LINK="https://www.petri.com/csc_3_wan_protocols_you_should_know" TEXT="3 WAN Protocols you should know: HDLC PPP and Frame ">
