			<node ID="ID_1589171163" TEXT="Carrier-sense multiple access with collision avoidance (CSMA/CA) in computer networking is a network multiple access method in which carrier sensing is used but nodes attempt to avoid collisions by beginning transmission only after the channel is sensed to be idle. When they do transmit nodes transmit their packet data in its entirety." />
