			<node ID="ID_1951640818" TEXT="Session Management in HTTP;  Computer Network | TCP Timers. TCP uses several timers to ensure that excessive delays are not encountered during communications. Several of these timers are elegant handling problems that are not immediately obvious at first analysis. Each of the timers used by TCP is examined in the following sections which " />
