			<node ID="ID_848362903" TEXT="TCP uses multiple timers (at least conceptually) to do its work. The most important of these is the RTO (Retransmission TimeOut). When a segment is sent a retransmission timer is started. If the segment is acknowledged before the timer expires the timer is stopped." />
