		<node ID="ID_1980404504" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_TCP_and_UDP_port_numbers" TEXT="List of TCP and UDP port numbers - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_626681761" TEXT="This is a list of TCP and UDP port numbers used by protocols of the application layer of the Internet protocol suite for the establishment of host-to-host connectivity. The Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) and the User Datagram Protocol (UDP) needed only one port for full-duplex" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_210107337" LINK="https://www.difference.wiki/tcp-vs-udp/" TEXT="Difference Between TCP vs. UDP &#8211; Difference Wiki">
			<node ID="ID_53433343" TEXT="One is known as Transmission Control Protocol while the other is called User Datagram Protocol. The main difference between these two is that TCP uses connections to send and receive data over the internet while UDP does not require connections to send data. In TCP data is sent over the network quickly but in UDP data is sent in different segments." />
